-- Standard Bank Hires Corfield as Emerging Credit Analyst
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a
-- 2012-03-27T14:31:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/standard-bank-hires-corfield-as-emerging-credit-analyst-1-.html
Natalia Corfield joined  Standard
Bank  Group Ltd. as a corporate-credit analyst covering emerging
markets.  Corfield, who will be based in New York and report to
Johannesburg, South Africa-based chief economist and global head
of research Goolam Ballim, was at ING Groep NV for two years
until December when the company cut its group focusing on  Latin
America  dollar debt. She had previously worked in a similar
position at Dresdner Kleinwort in London.  At Standard Bank, Corfield will cover Latin America,
Central and Eastern Europe and African credits.  “Natalia is prolific in her analyses, very well regarded
in the market and exudes a professional authority that will add
further stature to the Standard Bank Research team,” Ballim
wrote in an e-mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in  New York  at 
